getDisposedGenerationCount() - Method in class fr.ddspstl.DDS.samples.Sample
 
getDisposedGenerationCount() - Method in interface org.omg.dds.sub.Sample
For each instance the middleware internally maintains two counts: the disposedGenerationCount and noWritersGenerationCount, relative to each DataReader: The disposedGenerationCount and noWritersGenerationCount are initialized to zero when the DataReader first detects the presence of a never-seen-before instance. The disposedGenerationCount is incremented each time the instanceState of the corresponding instance changes from NOT_ALIVE_DISPOSED to ALIVE. The noWritersGenerationCount is incremented each time the instanceState of the corresponding instance changes from NOT_ALIVE_NO_WRITERS to ALIVE. The disposedGenerationCount and noWritersGenerationCount available in the Sample capture a snapshot of the corresponding counters at the time the sample was received.

getNoWritersGenerationCount() - Method in class fr.ddspstl.DDS.samples.Sample
 
getNoWritersGenerationCount() - Method in interface org.omg.dds.sub.Sample
For each instance the middleware internally maintains two counts: the disposedGenerationCount and noWritersGenerationCount, relative to each DataReader: The disposedGenerationCount and noWritersGenerationCount are initialized to zero when the DataReader first detects the presence of a never-seen-before instance. The disposedGenerationCount is incremented each time the instanceState of the corresponding instance changes from NOT_ALIVE_DISPOSED to ALIVE. The noWritersGenerationCount is incremented each time the instanceState of the corresponding instance changes from NOT_ALIVE_NO_WRITERS to ALIVE. The disposedGenerationCount and noWritersGenerationCount available in the Sample capture a snapshot of the corresponding counters at the time the sample was received.
